OL,6,FIt was the Crown's case that the "non-
OL,7,Faccidental" and "catastrophic" brain
OL,8,Finjuries suffered by Lewis in November
OL,9,F2015 - which a number of medical
OL,10,Fprofessionals determined were as a
OL,11,Fresult of the baby being shaken -
OL,12,Fplayed a significant role in his death.
OL,14,FOne doctor describing the brain injury
OL,15,Fwhich he believed was caused by
OL,16,Fshaking as "one of the "most severe"
OL,17,Fhe has seen in his ten years of
OL,18,Fpractice and determined it was
OL,19,Fsustained within a 24-hour period
OL,20,Fprior to Lewis being admitted to
OL,21,Fhospital on November 20, 2015.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/15
