OL,4,Cinfant son
OL,6,FThe medical professional also revealed
OL,7,Fthat the brain injury was akin to
OL,8,Fhaving been sustained in a road
OL,9,Ftraffic accident or a fall from "an
OL,10,Fenormous height."
OL,12,FWhen he gave evidence last week,
OL,13,FRowland admitted telling lies "here
OL,14,Fand there" to police in the aftermath
OL,15,Fof his son's death - but denied
OL,16,Finjuring his son.
OL,18,FFrom the witness box, Rowland accepted
OL,19,Fhis son had sustained injuries but
OL,20,Fdenied he was the one responsible.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/15
